  "description": "Restrict row-level access based on user authorization. Key topics: DCL is a SEPARATE artifact from the CDS view — file extension .asr. The CDS view must have @AccessControl.authorizationCheck: #CHECK. DCL uses ASPECT = PVZM to define mapping between fields and auth objects.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Key Learning Points",
      "description": "<div class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed\"><div class=\"flex items-start gap-2 mb-1.5\"><span class=\"text-brand-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0\">◆</span><span>DCL is a SEPARATE artifact from the CDS view — file extension .asr</span></div><div class=\"flex items-start gap-2 mb-1.5\"><span class=\"text-brand-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0\">◆</span><span>The CDS view must have @AccessControl.authorizationCheck: #CHECK</span></div><div class=\"flex items-start gap-2 mb-1.5\"><span class=\"text-brand-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0\">◆</span><span>DCL uses ASPECT = PVZM to define mapping between fields and auth objects</span></div><div class=\"flex items-start gap-2 mb-1.5\"><span class=\"text-brand-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0\">◆</span><span>Implicit access control is based on PFCG authorization object fields</span></div><div class=\"flex items-start gap-2 mb-1.5\"><span class=\"text-brand-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0\">◆</span><span>DCL can restrict: SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE (per operation)</span></div></div>"
    },
